ublic criticism of their actions to avoid drawing attention to brutal counterinsurgency practices such as the use of torture during interrogation. Some of the topics discussed in the book, such as the use of violence against civilians, the desire to uphold human rights values while simultaneously employing brutal methods, and the dynamic of wars waged in the glare of the media, are of critical interest to scholars, lawyers, and government officials dealing with the conflicts in Iraq and Afghanistan, and those to come in the future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aCounterinsurgencyzCyprus. 0aCounterinsurgencyzNorthern Ireland. 0aCounterinsurgencyzYemen (Republic)zAden. 0aHuman rightszCyprus. 0aHuman rightszNorthern Ireland. 0aHuman rightszYemen (Republic)zAden. 0aPostcolonialismzGreat Britain. 4aHistory. 4aMilitary History. 4aSecurity Studies. 7aHISTORY / Military / Wars & Conflicts (Other).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066587108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2018 Englishz978311060403008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2018z9783110603149oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501714672zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501714672423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501714672/original  a978-3-11-060403-0  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-066587-1  Cornell University Pr